EDITORS COMMENTS

Thunderbird II soars into action at the Slough film studios, capturing the essence of 1960s science fiction on set. This iconic photograph, taken by George Greenwell in October 1965, transports us back to a time when imagination knew no bounds. As Thunderbirds enthusiasts will recall, this remarkable model aircraft played a pivotal role in the beloved Thunderbirds series. The image showcases the meticulous attention to detail that went into creating these miniature wonders for filming purposes. The Slough film studios served as the perfect backdrop for bringing futuristic adventures to life, and Thunderbird II takes center stage here. Its sleek design and vibrant colors evoke a sense of awe and wonder even today. This print from Memory Lane Prints allows us to relive those thrilling moments when our favorite heroes embarked on daring missions against all odds. It serves as a nostalgic reminder of an era where practical effects reigned supreme before CGI took over. Whether you were captivated by Thunderbirds' gripping storylines or marveled at its imaginative models and sets, this snapshot encapsulates it all. Let your imagination take flight once more as you gaze upon Thunderbird II's triumphant takeoff – a testament to the enduring legacy of this groundbreaking series.
